STEPS TO BECOME AN NP 🩺✨🫶🏼 // @the.nurse.sarah

1. Become an RN! I went to a 4 year BSN program but you can do ADN ➡️MSN in step #3 
2. +/- Get nursing experience. Some people skip this and go straight to grad school which is totally ok! I started a year into peds nursing and I had 4 years of full time nursing experience by the time I graduated! 
3. Enroll in a MSN or DNP program- I went MSN but DNP isn’t off the table! 🎓
4. Earn your NP License 😊 I sat for my FNP boards 💫

💉INJECTION ANGLES REVIEW 📐
(save this!!!) 

INTRAMUSCULAR (IM) 
🎯: Muscle (think IN to the muscle 💭) 
📐: 90 degrees 
Common rx: most vaccines (HepB, Hib, HepA…) certain antibiotics and meds (EpiPen)
Common sites: vastus lateralis (👶🏻) , deltoid 

SUBCUTANEOUS (SubQ) 
🎯: fatty layer between the skin and muscle 
📐: pinch 🤏🏽 the skin + 45-90 degrees
Common rx: insulin, heparin, some vaccines (MMR, varicella) 
Common sites: lower abdomen, upper outer arms, upper outer thighs 

INTRADERMAL (ID) 
🎯: dermis (layer beneath the epidermis, superficial!!)
📐: 10-15 degrees
Common uses: allergy or TB testing 
Common sites: forearm, upper back

make sure you rotate sites !!! 😊💉✨

POSITANO ITINERARY + TIPS 🫶🏼✨
by popular demand, compiled our Positano deets!! Save this post! We can’t wait to go back 🇮🇹🍝

where we stayed: @covodeisaraceni - loved that it was right on the water, had an epic terrace with an infinity pool!

what we did: day trip to Capri (make sure to bring Dramamine!!), explore the secluded private beaches via boat, Arienzo beach club (don’t ball out on the first row, any row will do), night swimming in the med ✨

where we ate: Chez Black (iconic restaurant and right on the water, make RSVPs), Covo Dei Saranecini (on the water), Arienzo Beach Club, and the best gelato at Buca di Bacco!

Traveling with dietary restrictions: keep your injections in your carry on and if it needs to be temp controlled, make sure your hotel has a fridge! bring your safety foods- I brought a whole checked luggage of @liveowyn, have your epis always on you, scrub the menus beforehand!

its time for a little re-intro!! 🫶🏼 my name is Sarah! I’m a medical, cosmetic and surgical Dermatology Nurse Practitioner based out of California!! Prior to this role I was a Navy Nurse for 5+ years specializing in Peds with an emphasis in Oncology. Some facts about me:

+ I’m a twin! And my twin is also a nurse, who married a twin 😂
+ I was born and went to undergrad in Chicago! I grew up in San Diego 
+ I’m married to a fighter pilot, Xavy! We have a cavapoo named Kona 🐾
+ I love to draw and make art! I took a class when I studied abroad in Rome 
+ a perfect day for me is spent somewhere by the ocean, listening to Taylor Swift and reading ACOTAR 😋
+ I’m a libra! Which I feel is very fitting because I’m all about balance ⚖️

I’m super passionate about all things skin health, and I love making people look and feel their best. I love sharing my life in and out of scrubs, thanks for stopping by my little corner of the internet 🫶🏼
